project:
Houseplants cannot grow when root bound. They physically don’t have more space (Bawden-Davis, 2007).

If you haven’t seen new growth in a while it may be time to repot (Heather Blackmore, 2019).

To prevent mold from growing, don’t over water. Most house plants don’t need to be watered more than once a week (Zach, 2022). 
ZZ Plants shouldn’t be watered unless the soil is totally dry. Try once every two weeks (Bhatta, 2021).

Even though plants need light, too much sun damages carotenoids, chemicals used in regulation of photosynthesis (Holt et al., 2005). Even though plants need light, too much sun damages carotenoids, chemicals used in regulation of photosynthesis (Holt et al., 2005). Plants have limited ability to discharge extra light energy by shutting off their chlorophyl (Cupellini et al., 2020).

Drooping leaves, yellow spots, and crinkly leaves are all signs of sun damage (morgan, 2022).

Some plants need more water than others. Most are once a week, some are every 14 days (Student B, personal communication, April 19, 2023). 

For example, Aloe Vera only needs to be watered every 2-3 weeks. Avocado trees need every 3 days (Student D, personal communication, April 19, 2023).

ZZ plants don't need direct light. They thrive with 8-10 hours of indirect light. A light bulb won't hurt them but they certainly don't need it (Gurung, 2023).

Too much light can be harmful to plants. If the light is too bright, it can damage the leaves. Leaving in plant in light too long can disrupt its growth cycle (Andrew Courtney, n.d.).

One of your stems died from root rot. Too much mold and too much water can kill the roots (David Beaulieu, 2019). 

If a plant seems fine but then suddenly withers or dies, it is probably root rot (Millard Elizabeth, 2014).
Repotting is stressful for the plant but is important if the roots are crowded

If your plant is rootbound, it can’t grow any more. It might be rootbound if you see roots growing out the sides or bottom of the pot. (Craig Taylor, 2022)
Repotting stresses the plant. It may even lose a few leaves, but it should bounce back quicky. There will likely be some new growth soon (Hilton Carter, 2019 p87).

South facing windows get a lot more direct sunlight in the Northern Hemisphere (Megan Devine, 2020). 
It’s important to know your plants. Every plant is different (Julio Mendez, personal communication, April 18, 2023). 

Trial and error can help you make choices for your plant and figure out what works best (Student C, personal communication, April 19, 2023).
